                    <h3>What does Kjuicer allow?</h3>
                    <h2>READ LESS</h2>
                    <p><b>If you <i>kjuice</i> the text (i.e. highlight):</b></p>
                    <ul>
                        <li><b>EXTRACT</b> meaningful content on the fly;</li>
                        <li>Give it a <b>PRIORITY</b>;</li>
                        <li>Learn it <b>TWICE AS FAST</b>;</li>
                        <li>Make it accessible in <b>THREE CLICKS</b>... also for others.</li>
                    </ul>
                    <p><b>If it has been already <i><b>kjuiced</b></i>:</b></p>
                    You have three <b>BROWSABLE SUMMARIES</b> connected with the original text.
                </section>
                <section>
                    <p>Show how to find <b>IMPORTANT CONCEPTS</b>.
                    <p>Trasform, or let others transform, <b>TEXT</b> into a <b>ZOOMABLE</b> and <b>BROWSABLE</b> resource.</p>
                    <p>Allow reading also to those short of <b>TIME</b>.</p>
                </section>
                <section>
                    <p><b>SIMPLIFY</b> access to content that might be ignored</p>
